# Documentation SSOT and structure

## 1. Single source of truth

Each type of information lives in one place; others reference it.

| Type | Where |
|------|--------|
| spec/ | Normative contract (state machines, keys, invariants) |
| architecture/ | Diagrams and high-level flow |
| design/ | Redesign, migration, rollout plan |
| adr/ | Reasons for decisions |
| testing/ | Test strategy, scenarios, run modes |
| operations/ | High-level status only; no copy of spec/design |

Do not copy contract across documents. Root: `docs/state-snapshotter-rework/`. Extended ADR drafts live under `snapshot-rework/` at repo root — keep **normative summaries** in sync with `docs/state-snapshotter-rework/spec/system-spec.md`; do not treat `snapshot-rework/` alone as SSOT for implementable contract. When deprecating a doc: mark in README or file header; point to new source.

## 2. Document boundaries (explicit)

- **spec/** — normative contract only.
- **architecture/** — diagrams and high-level flow; not normative.
- **design/** — redesign / migration / rollout plan; does not become status.
- **adr/** — why the decision was made; not edited as current specification.
- **testing/** — test strategy, scenarios, run modes; references spec, does not copy it.
- **operations/** — high-level only; no long spec/design/TODO/state machine dumps (see operations-status-update and status-high-level-only).

In docs, separate clearly: **implemented** | **current target** | **planned/future** | **legacy/deprecated**.

## 3. Structure

```
docs/state-snapshotter-rework/
  spec/system-spec.md
  architecture/overview.md (diagrams may add system-overview.puml)
  design/implementation-plan.md (and other design notes)
  adr/README.md (long-form ADR may stay in snapshot-rework/ until migrated)
  testing/e2e-testing-strategy.md
  operations/project-status.md
```

## 4. Before changing code

Read spec/system-spec.md; if redesign — design/; if touching a decision — adr/. On contract change: update spec; run e2e checks; add ADR if needed. New mechanism: design → spec → tests → code.

## 5. Development order

**design → spec → tests → code.** If code and spec disagree, fix code or update spec; do not leave inconsistent.

## 6. Naming

Docs: `kebab-case.md`. ADR: `adr-XXXX-short-title.md`. Diagrams: `system-overview.puml`, unified-snapshot / manifest flow diagrams as needed. E2E scripts: `NN_description.sh` when used under `images/state-snapshotter-controller/test/` or repo root smoke.

## 7. Before PR

Spec matches code; unit and envtest pass; e2e not broken (see controller-redeploy-and-remote-e2e); docs updated; critical changes → operations-status-update; stages → delivery-gating.

## 8. Main rule

Docs must answer: **What must the system do?** → spec. **Why is it designed so?** → ADR. **How to verify?** → testing.
